242010-01-26
Memorandum Order that ArcelorMittals complaint has failed to allege facts that amount to more than a sheer possibility that a defendant has acted unlawfully. Iqbal, 129 S.Ct. at 1949. The fact that the illustration prepared by Jewell included the allegedly correct formula is consistent with Jewells liability, but, in light of the other facts alleged--as well as those facts not alleged--by ArcelorMittal in the complaint, the complaint stops short of the line between possibility and plausibility of entitlement to relief. Id. (internal quotations omitted). Accordingly, Counts I and III of ArcelorMittals complaint are dismissed without prejudice pursuant to Rule 12(b)(6). Because Count II is contingent upon this courts rescission of the agreement, it, too, is dismissed without prejudice pursuant to Rule 12(b)(6). IV. ArcelorMittals complaint is dismissed without prejudice., This Document if filed under Seal. Copies by e-mail to all parties 1-26-2010. Judge Ann Aldrich on 1-26-2010. (K,V) (Entered: 01/26/2010)
252010-01-26
Judgment Entry that this action is dismissed without prejudice pursuant to Rule 58 of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure. Document filed under seal. Parties notified by e-mail on 1-26-2010 Judge Ann Aldrich (K,V) (Entered: 01/26/2010)

  












































